===Verb===
{{en-verb|quits|quitting|'''quit''' ''or'' '''[[quitted]]'''}}
# To [[stop]] doing something.
# To [[give up]] a [[habit]].
# To [[leave]] a [[locality]].
# {{past of|[[quit]]}}

====Usage notes====
The past tense of ''quit'' is now ''quit'' for most speakers and writers; dictionaries usually allow ''quitted'' as an alternative, but it is rare or nonexistent in North America and Australia, and outnumbered by ''quit'' by about 16 to 1 in the [http://www.natcorp.ox.ac.uk/ British National Corpus]. 

